<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-09-01T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-09-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="154" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">822.002/108: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-01T18:00:00-05:00">September 1, 1931—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:28 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>44. By two Executive decrees of today Senator Pedro L. Nunez has been
                            appointed Minister of Finance and Presidential elections have been
                            called for October 20 and 21 in compliance with article No. 81 of the
                            constitution.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>